ommercialisation of products, there are still many skilled craftsman who continue to create elegant masterpieces with this stone.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.kraftstory.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/31.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-119 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://www.kraftstory.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/31.png\" alt=\"Marble art in India\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.kraftstory.com/marble-best-chowki-ganesh-en-4\">Shop Now</a>\r\n\r\nThe marble craft came into existence amongst Italian sculptors towards the end of the 16<sup>th</sup> century and gradually found its way through gifts to the Mughal emperor. From there on the journey of marble handicrafts started in India. With Agra being famous for its marble inlay work, Gujarat is also known for its marble sculptures from Ambaji. Rajasthan is one of has one of the best marble quarry in India, the craftsmen here follow the age old tradition of craving and sculpting images of gods and deities.  Jaipur is the centre of marble making and apart from sculptures of deities; they also create regular household items like plates, bowls, mortar, and pestle etc.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.kraftstory.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/21.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-118 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://www.kraftstory.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/21.png\" alt=\"marble art in India\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.kraftstory.com/home-decor/spiritual/pooja-thalis/ecraftindia-set-of-lord-ganesha-pooja-thali-and-mayur-chopra\">Shop Now</a>\r\n\r\nSome exclusive marble creations can have found their way into our store. At Kraftstory we take pride in being a one stop platform that showcases products which reflects Indian tradition in every step. All you have to do is look; we are a Pandora’s Box waiting to be explored. Our online shopping experience is replete with traditional and quirky creations by our artisans. Experience an unforgettable jo