age-347 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/bandhani_02.jpg\" alt=\"bandhani_02\" width=\"721\" height=\"583\" /></a>\r\n\r\nUsing the process of tie-dye, making a bandhani fabric is a highly skilled art. The technique of making this fabric involves dyeing a fabric which is then tied with a thread at several points. This creates a pattern of beautiful colours and designs. Bandhani pieces can be dyed in natural or artificial colours. This fabric looks best on churidar suits as the mix of colours and patterns are brought out best with the make of a churidar. While stitching it might be difficult and expensive, you can avail a large variety of bandhani made churidar suits through online shopping.\r\n<h2>Khadi</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/kadi.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-349 \" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/kadi-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"kadi\" width=\"721\" height=\"541\" /></a>\r\n\r\nKhadi is not just a cloth in India, it is a form of rebellion. A movement started by Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, Khadi cloth was used to rebel against the British. This cloth is woven from cotton and silk or wool. They are spun into yarn on a spinning wheel called the charkha. Very popular among men kurtas, the Khadi cloth is widely accepted in fashion circles. To give it a stiffer feel, the cloth is also starched at times.\r\n<h2>Brocade</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/brocade.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-348 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/brocade.jpg\" alt=\"brocade\" width=\"694\" height=\"416\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOften made in coloured silks and with or without gold and silver threads, Brocade is a richly decorative woven fabric. Typically woven on a draw loom, the brocade fabric is made using the supplementary waft technique. In this technique, the cloth is woven in such a way that it gives the appearance of the weave that it was embroidered on. Due to its richness, this fabric can be used to make many various kinds of ethnic wear like Anarkali suits, churidar suits, sarees and many more.\r\n<h2>Ajrakh Printing</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ajrakh.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-346 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ajrakh.jpg\" alt=\"ajrakh\" width=\"759\" height=\"318\" /></a>\r\n\r\nSpecially used for making beautiful shawls, the Ajrakh fabric is perfect for this cold weather! Specially found in Kutch, Gujarat and Rajasthan, this fabric is made from natural dyes. The dyes included in making this fabric include both vegetable dyes and mineral dyes, although Indigo dye is the key. Known for the geometric patterns, the shawls are elegant and stylish yet extremely comfortable and can keep you really warm. In order to get the extra ordinary geometry on the cloth, a method of printing called woodblock printing is used. In this method, prints were transferred on the cloth by pressing wooden blocks with the print hard on the fabric.\r\n<h2>Suzani</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/suzani.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-351 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/suzani.jpg\" alt=\"suzani\" width=\"654\" height=\"525\" /></a>\r\n\r\nSlightly different from the others mentioned, the Suzani is an embroidered and decorative tribal textile which is made in Tajikistan, Kazakhstan and many other Central Asian countries.  Originally made for the Central Asian brides as part of their dowry, these vintage fabrics are specially made for everyday use. You can find this fabric for sarees, Patiala suits and churidar suits while online shopping.\r\n<h2>Kalamkari</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/kalamkari-paintings.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-350 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/kalamkari-paintings.jpg\" alt=\"kalamkari-paintings\" width=\"700\" height=\"408\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere are two different types of Kalamakari art in India. One is the Srikalahasti style while the other is the Machilipatnam style. The Srikalahasti is probably the most ancient work of art which is completely handmade. A ‘kalam’ or a pen is used for free hand drawing on the fabric and then colour is filled in. The kalamkari art owes its popularity to Smt. Kamaladevi Chattopadhay who publicized about this art and is the first Chairperson of the All India Handicrafts Board. The art of Kalamkari uses completely natural dyes and is one of the most difficult artwork which requires tremendous skill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThese are only a few types of handmade fabrics that are used. There are many more. These fabrics not only make the dress look more elegant and beautiful, they also give a patriotic feeling to the wearer! You can easily find handmade stitched fabric Anarkali suits, Patiala Suits, Salwar Kameez and Churidar suits online shopping! Like Narendra Modi says, Live in India, Make in India!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/KRAFTSTORY.jpg\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-339 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/KRAFTSTORY.jpg\" alt=\"KRAFTSTORY\" width=\"804\" height=\"466\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Lost World of Handmade Fabrics','','publish','open','open','','the-lost-world-of-handmade-fabrics','','','2015-11-30 16:19:42','2015-11-30 16:19:42','',0,'http://blog.kraftstory.com/?p=345',0,'post','',0),(346,4,'2015-11-30 16:08:13','2015-11-30 16:08:13','','ajrakh','','inherit','open','open','','ajrakh','','','2015-11-30 16:08:13','2015-11-30 16:08:13','',345,'http://blog.kraftstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ajrakh.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(347,4,'2015-11-30 16:08:16','2015-11-30 16:08:16','','bandhani_02','','inherit','open','open','','bandhan